11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 567.4c of Title 59, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. 1. An Advanced Practice Registered Nurse recognized by the
16 Oklahoma Board of Nursing as a Certified Nurse Practitioner,
17 Clinical Nurse Specialist, or Certified Nurse-Midwife who has
18 completed a minimum of six thousand two hundred forty (6,240) hours
19 of practice with prescriptive authority supervised by a physician
20 may apply to the Oklahoma Board of Nursing for authority to
21 prescribe and order independent of supervision.
22 2. The application for independent prescriptive authority shall
23 include proof that the Certified Nurse Practitioner, Clinical Nurse
24 Specialist, or Certified Nurse-Midwife:
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2298 Page 2

1 a. holds a valid, current license in the appropriate
2 Advanced Practice Registered Nurse role issued by the
3 Board and is in good standing with the Board, and
4 b. has completed a minimum of six thousand two hundred
5 forty (6,240) hours of practice with prescriptive
6 authority supervised by a physician. This
7 subparagraph shall not be construed to exclude
8 practice hours with supervised prescriptive authority
9 obtained prior to the effective date of this act from
10 being counted toward the hours required in this
11 subparagraph.
12 3. Independent prescriptive authority granted under this
13 subsection shall be valid until the expiration of the current
14 license to practice and may be renewed upon application to the Board
15 at the same time and for the same period as the renewal of the
16 license to practice.
17 B. The Board shall review any application submitted under this
18 section and shall approve or deny the application, stating the
19 reason or reasons for denial, if denied. If denied, the applicant
20 may reapply using the process prescribed by subsection A of this
21 section.
22 C. The Board may suspend or revoke independent prescriptive
23 authority granted under this section for good cause at any time.
24
