1 D. The Board may establish a fee for the review of initial and
2 renewal applications under the provisions of this section.
3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 567.5b of Title 59, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. An Advanced Practice Registered Nurse, or the employer of
7 the Advanced Practice Registered Nurse on his or her behalf, shall
8 carry malpractice insurance or demonstrate proof of financial
9 responsibility in a minimum amount of One Million Dollars
10 ($1,000,000.00) per occurrence and Three Million Dollars
11 ($3,000,000.00) in the aggregate per year. The requirement to carry
12 malpractice insurance shall extend only to the Advanced Practice
13 Registered Nurse, and not be construed as to require the Advance
14 Practice Registered Nurse to provide malpractice insurance coverage
15 to any supervising or collaborating physician.
16 B. An Advanced Practice Registered Nurse who is employed by or
17 under contract with a federal agency that carries malpractice
18 insurance in any amount on behalf of the Advanced Practice
19 Registered Nurse shall be deemed in compliance with subsection A of
20 this section when practicing under such federal employment or
21 contract. However, to the extent the Advanced Practice Registered
22 Nurse practices outside of such federal employment or contract, the
23 Advanced Practice Registered Nurse, or his or her employer, shall
24 comply with subsection A of this section.
